items.text: Porridge stall at the corner
Many great food options here. I have to go again. Lucky Wanton Noodle really did make me fee lucky. Also spotted ginger chicken soup and ginormous es kacang.
Peanut ice-kachang is a must-try! Shiok ah!
Wantan noodles: Lucky (stall 02-33). I come here 4 succulent, well-caramelised char siew, & crispy wantans! Still find bak pok bits (fried pork lard), addg fragrance 2 d alrdy mouth-waterg dish
Try the Lucky wanton noodle. Good value for money
Ming Kee Cooked Food is a must try too,  from speciality meat eggs to curry chicken and their pork chop. to their fried fish nuggets shaped in circle. must try :)
The Lor Mee at #02-20 sucks. My grandmother at Home can cook better Lor Mee than this...
The food centre is now back open. Many stalls have changed since it was closed for almost a year, so many of the tips here are obsolete.
Try the famous Ice kacang... Selling at $1.50.
Tried Nissan Thai food's phad Thai and Tom yum. Not bad. Must try. Authentic Thai food!!
Tanjong pagar fried kway teow nice - 02-09
Ali Nachiya Biriyani
Lucky wtm is cheap and delicious. Try their green chillie!
Try the basil leaf chicken here!! Very nice...
Upper Cross Street Soya Sauce Chicken: chicken tender but not as tender as Michelin Star, noodles bouncy like Basketball, dumplings crunchy with chestnuts, and free chicken butts if you ask. 7/10
Issan thai food not bad, friendly priced. Had the basil leaves rice w egg and omelet. Will try other dishes the next time.
Try the Japanese cuisine tori karaage set... Super crispy and nice chicken!!!
Rong xing(sisters) yong tau fu nice meh? Tried the soup quite light and tasteless leh...
满满hokkien noodles!! :)
must try the wan ton mee, best...Cantonese style, old couple selling, stall is near to shun li coffee stall...juz quote 靓仔。
Good food, good prices but very hot and a pain to get a seat
Loh Mee is good, can try the nasi lemak too~ try out the ice kachang with peanut topping.
On the ground floor are fruit and flower stalls.
Herbal chicken soup, 3.80sgd for soup only. Very nice and healthy. Tymms
The Issan Thai food here is very good!! Tian xin Dou hua  shui also good
DON'T eat the laksa It's like colour water. Tasteless n thin.
Hot and very crowded during lunch time
cheap and great soya drink with grass jelly only @ $0.80!!
Try the Kazan Japanese cuisine #02-18.  Pretty decent salmon teriyaki set and chicken teriyaki set. With a cup of not so salty miso soup
The fruits sold here are fresh and cheap.
Kazan Jap food is really pretty good! Had e Pork curry rice. Pork is well cooked n crispy, but rice can be cooked better n more generous.
The fruit juice stand is great in the middle of center. 4th row.
Fried carrot cake: There r 2 stalls. Prefer stall 02-51 as it's less oily, & more imptly, more flavourful!
Peanut ice kachang
The cheapest cappuccino on town can be found here for 2.80! They use lavazza coffee and a real expresso machine.
Food centre finally reopen after 1 year. There are some new stalls to check out too...!!!
Best mee Siam n mee rebus must try arh
Try Annie peanut ice kachang, it's nice
Wei ji wanton noodles is a must try
The fish soup at Soon Li Fish Soup & Porridge #02-42
Daily Greens - Great affordable pasta & salad. Also, free soup with every purchase as part of their opening promotion. MUST visit.
Good variety of food here. Cheap n reasonable.
Fish ball noodle is decent!!
Try the chap cai peng at Ming Kee Cooked Food at #02-25. Remember to ask for their excellent chilli sauce!
No more Annie's peanut ice kachang. Fried shark lor mee sounded interesting but didn't really live up to hype.
Briased duck rice set for $3!
Nice Japanese food
lekerrrrrrrrrr
Kazan Japanese Cuisine #02-18, 4 out of 5 stars. Recommended meal set: salmon teriyaki, chicken teriyaki, tori karaage, and katsu (pork) curry don. Be warned, long queue during lunch hour.
A must try Japan Cuisine ! The boss is so friendly & nice. Next up definitly leave it to the Ming Kee Cooked Food, serve with delicious mixed rice~
Go try the Nasi lemak at Pandan Leaf Nasi Lemak. Freaking cheap! Review - http://prodigious.sg/pandan-leaf-nasi-lemak/
Awesome paper-wrapped herbal chicken soup + rice at #02-17.
Closed from 1 Mar 2013 to Mar 2014 for renovations.
Should try japanese popular dishes and pasta at KITCHEN@WORK, cook by 20+years experience Chef Roger!
Try the muffins from chocolate 'n' spice bakery! You won't regret :)

For Homemade Soya Bean, Tahuae & Chin Chau lovers... Head over to #02-41. A big glass cost a dollar, expensive but worth it. I mean these days day by day these kinda drinks stalls are goin extinct. :(
Fruits are very fresh!
Vegetarian options: yong tau foo, lontong, thunder tea rice, local desserts, beancurd, grass jelly, fruits, mushroom hor fun, chai tow kway
Huge food portion for the basil chicken @$4.50 only at #02-23 Nissan Thai food
Kopi (local coffee): Compared several stalls & asked some stall-holders. Ah Teck Coffee Stall #02-24 is d favourite. D flavour & taste were smoother. A close 2nd is nearby Ka Fei Xiang #02-19
Annie's peanut ice kachang must try.
#stervylicious #nasilemak - best day ! Its TGIF!! N what a sumptuous brekky I had today.:) Tried the famous nasi lemak Chinese stall...  Try it if u haven't - pandan leaf nasi lemak/#02-25.
You gotta try the Pandan Leaf Nasi Lemak, cheap with awesome ingredients!
Try out every menu available at Tiong Bahru Roasted Meat stall. You will not be disappointed. Dry Dumpling noodles will definitely win your heart.
Love the Niang Doufu and the tasty soup. The stall is the one by the sisters, facing the Duxton HDB Flats direction, right next to the stairs.
Must-try: Annie's Peanut Ice Kachang!
Nice fried mee n bee hoon ,chee cheong fun , yam cake n porridge #02-27. good .
Basil Leaves Chicken is a must try :)
Wanton mee stall beside the fruit juice stall= damn good+cheap! Must try!
Fantastic hawker center with a good variety of stalls. Everything I've tried has been tasty and best of all quite reasonably priced!
#02-48. fish ball noodles. Good n cheap. $2.50 =)
Simply loves the Hakka yong tau hu here. But don't know why both sisters spilt to open their own stall?
The japanese fast food stall is a must try for Japanese food lovers!
Cheap n nice bfast set come with 2egg , 2slice of bread , coffee/tea .
Annie's Peanut Ice Kachang had moved to Ghom Moh and will not return. The store replacing it is also selling peanut ice kachang! No idea whether is it nice.
New soup bar. #02-51
林记鱼汤板面 is my fave! Try the tom yum mee hoon kueh. Home cook feel!
Try Herbal Kitchen's signature herbal chicken! Chicken is so soft it peels off from d bone! Shiok! #02-11 stall
Try the lucky wanton noodle. It's good.
this place will be closed for Reno/upgrading from 1 Mar 2013 to 1st quarter of 2014!
If you are char kway teow afficianado, you should have this tanjong pagar fried kway teow on your "bee there done that" list.
The curry rice is expensive...;-( the Thai food nice
Still my favourite among the other stalls!!
#02-27 must try their fried bee hoon, yam cake and Chee qiong fun...
Hawker has re-opened. Yay!!
Braised duck rice set for only $3!!! So worth it:))
